The first cohort will consist of Bao NFT holders as they are our OG supporters. 

The application process will slowly open up to everyone in the following cohorts.

This is not just launching more NFTs either.

We are supporting new musicians, actors, & podcasters.

Every project voted into our cohort will receive:

a) 2 ETH 
b) Support of our community & team to share their story with the world
c) Bespoke advisory and commercial guidance

The core part of Fortune Friends Club’s mission is to empower and celebrate Asian creatives.

Especially those that are just getting started, without a huge following already.

We want to be their voice and platform to share their unique story.

As people who grew up in an Asian households, we know first hand what it was like to constantly be nagged to become a doctor / lawyer / engineer. 

There was a general lack of support for “risky” creative careers. 

We want to fix that.

The Asian Creatives Fund was established to run a great experiment:

If we provide financial support to budding creatives, can we enable more people leap into pursuing a creative career?

Further, combining that with our community's loving support, how far can we go? 🤔

The day is finally here.

Tomorrow, we'll be showcasing the very best applications to our Creatives Fund, and enabling our community to vote on the first cohort.

We are beyond excited!

Dumplings are also a symbol of wealth 🌟 It holds a shape that is similar to the ancient Chinese gold ingot. So eating them is a sign of good fortune!

In Chinese culture, dumplings bring people together. Combining different dumplings together which you'll see a lot at events like Lunar New Year signifies togetherness. It represents how we value working and being together, and the more you eat, the stronger this bond becomes 💙

Why is our base layer character a BAO? 🥟🙊

This has a double meaning for us. In Chinese – Bao as in bāo zi (包子) means steamed bun, and bao in bǎo zàng (宝藏) means precious treasure. https://t.co/jbTHJWU907

Our mission at FFC is to empower & celebrate Asian culture, thats why we've brou…

...and of course, Bao Best Friends 😚💙

Remember, we're aiming to build a brand. Great product & brand takes time to build, and we want to do it right. Trust the process & join us in our journey to bridge East <> West ✨

🥟 How do holders benefit?

We’ll soon include a write up on all the above. But for now, holders can access:
≫ 1st round of investment from the fund
≫ Exclusive food events & menus globally!
≫ Giveaways
≫ 1st access/discounts/giveaways
≫ Airdrops & future NFT drops...

❌ What have we deprioritised?

Global decentralised lottery. We haven’t punted this, but for now, we’re likely going to launch fun mini-games on our website instead. We’ve chosen to prioritise bridging the East and West with our product & experiences.

≫ We’re exploring a consultant/advisory angle for other NFT projects. We’ll start by pushing NFT content on our experiences and learnings (trust me, there’s a LOT :cold_face:), before adopting a more high-touch model with Asian celebrities, brands and franchises.
≫ We’re exploring a curated marketplace which showcases pieces from Asian artists all over the world. This could be clothing, decor, NFT art and more.

🚀 So, we’ve adjusted our roadmap to reflect what we’ve observed from all of us growing together.

≫ Fortune Launchpad brought forward 2 quarters to focus on supporting early-stage founders/teams scale. We'll help founders get global distribution on their product launches.

In the past few weeks, building this incredible community has taught us a few things:
1. We have a tonne of Asian creatives in FFC!
2. Our DMs are flooded with NFT founders in FFC launching their own project
3. Magical moments in DC revolve around games, events & friendly vibes

A main-belt asteroid, discovered on December 31, 1994, was named 10160 Totoro after the film's central character. ✨

Totoro resonates with us because he transforms scary situations into silly ones.

The film's central character, Totoro, is as famous among Asian children as Winnie-the-Pooh is among British ones.

• We're now working with @SerpentAU to ensure our DC + team accounts are properly audited and secured. He's uncovered a scammer bot with admin permissions and has deactivated it.

• We're creating process controls around best practices for working with partners to ensure we don't fall for any social engineering. This will be aligned across the dev team + mods.
• Ensuring we have at least 1 person on the team awake and on DC at all times.

What we're doing to fix this //

• Security hygiene. Each person in the dev team has refreshed their PW, created new accounts if needed and updated 2FA. 
• We've updated passwords and 2FA for all social handles.

Any attempts to send messages, delete channels, lock channels or warn people, our messages were immediately countered.
8AM
Dyno bot was hacked & spammed all channels to direct members to the fake website.

5:15AM - 7AM
People started "minting" - sending ETH to a wallet address on a fake website.
7AM
QueenBao & Baowzer are online. Despite trying to secure Discord, there wasn't anything we could do while BaoBao's account was compromised.

4:30AM 
All mods were gone. They then removed all channels & special roles. Anyone who spoke up about a possible hack was banned. Tickets were removed. 
4:33AM
Server stats were updated to reflect a new mint date. 
5:15AM
An event in DC was scheduled: "Minting is now Live".

4:21AM
1st action from BaoBao's account - they created a webhook spidey bot in our Discord. In the next 5 minutes all language channels were removed. All channel permissions were overridden. 
4:27AM
Banned or DC Lead and ALL of our global mods, and updated admin team roles.

More specifics on the details of how this hack works is outlined by Serpent here: https://t.co/QS9kxWhlax

This conversation went down around 4PM AEDT yesterday, giving the hacker time to study our DC and learn the dev team's active hours.

The morning of....

BaoBao & BaoKong being amazing on partnerships, jumped on this straight away. Once inside, it seemed like an official Discord with Mina greeting them there. 

As soon as we entered in that code, we gave the hacker access to bypass our 2FA.

A user (0xSophia#0001) posed as a partner from Wonderpals - a project we're really excited to work with. They reached out to us for a collab and said that the Wonderpals DC is closed, but you could use this specific code to get in for a WL role.

Our DC was compromised. We're so sorry Baos -- we're going to fix it.

Hopefully this thread serves as a warning for other projects to learn from our mistakes.

Why they are important? 

Well, the internet is famously good at making content nearly free. 😀

But for that precise reason, it is terrible at making content expensive, which at times it should be, particularly when creators pour tens/hundreds of hours into it. 😪

5/

They are artifacts of digital communities and they derive value to the extent they reinforce that community’s values, norms, language and memes.🤝
